description:
&lt;p&gt;The Haematology inpatient unit is looking for a Band 5 Staff Nurse to join the team on Tudor Ward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is a varied and exciting role with opportunity for professional and personal development within the challenging and rewarding specialities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a Haematology/Endocrinology 24 bedded ward which provides excellent holistic care to patients with a variety of conditions. We are seeking an individual who will support the ward as we start our inpatient chemotherapy service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, adaptable nurse, preferably with experience in haematology/oncology and solid interest/experience in cytotoxic chemotherapy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will support you in your clinical development: there is a vast range of in house training and you must be willing to attend university courses relevant to the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a fantastic opportunity to join a committed and enthusiastic team and to make a real difference in patients’ life.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Samuel Vacca – Ward Manager – Tudor Ward&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ext 7559 or mobile 07551824960&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
